Last year, the Police and Border Guard Board (PPA) extended and issued a record 13,000 residence permits to third-country nationals who have mostly travelled to Estonia to work, study or stay with their families.
For example, last year it was decided to issue a temporary residence permit to 6,702 foreigners, but last year the number was 4,928.
