Crop fields were also badly damaged in the storm, and the newspaper reported that "the party's primary organizations must be the inspiration and direction for both the clean-up and the harvesting."
Hurricanes can be said to occur when the average wind speed exceeds 32.7 m/s.
The wind speed record in Estonia is from 2 November 1969, when Ruhnu measured the wind speed at 48 m/s.
